<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2570: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-11T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            11, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>6264. Following telegram of December 8, 4 p.m., from Tokyo:</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text of telegram printed on <ref target="#pg_545">page
                                    545</ref>.]</p>
                            <p>Department has referred matter to American Group and will advise
                                later decision reached. We are practically recommending acceptance
                                of the suggestion.</p>
                            <p>Repeat to Paris as No. 9313.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>